AUTHORITIES in Lindi have deferred marking of the Malaria Day which was to be held here at national level today due to fears of the imminent Tropical Cyclone Kenneth which is forecast to hit Lindi, Mtwara and Ruvuma regions. The announcement to postpone the celebrations was made by Lindi District Commissioner, Mr Shaibu Ndemanga,shortly after government officials and citizens had arrived at Pilipili grounds ready for the event. The Minister for Health, Community Development, Gender, Elderly and Children, Ms Ummy Mwalimu, was expected to grace the event. Tanzania Meteorological Agency (TMA) warned in Dar es Salaam on Wednesday that the cyclone, which is forecast to make a landfall in Mozambique by midday tomorrow, is likely to hit Lindi, Mtwara and Ruvuma regions.